<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
After reading it a few times I think it was 'nerfed' somewhat, thought I hate that term, based on this line:<P> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR><BR>* If you or your group do less than half of the damage to the monster, the pet gets between 25% and 50% of the experience, depending on how much damage it did.<BR><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Before, according to all I've read, if a pet outdamaged the entire group (did 51% of total damage) the pet took an equal share of exp, ie: 1/7 (maybe 1/6 depending on what they consider a share).<P>Now, if the pet outdamages the group it will take 25-50% of the total exp, ie: 1/4-1/2.  A much larger percentage.<P>Not that I care, it will still be impossible to outdamage the pet solo, which means I still get half, just like before.  And grouping, any two comparable melee (L59/60 who've spent ~27pts on AA's just like the DC'er) will most likely outdamage a DC pet unless the mob is ping-ponging which means the pet steals no exp, just like before.
</FONT>
