<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Imperial Crypt Guardian's comparison is most useful.  Unfortunately, it needs correcting.  I've elaborated and added changes, which show that there are indeed slight nerfs present in the new code.  <P>OLD VERSION, SOLO:<BR>-Pet does more than half damage, takes half exp.<BR>- Pet does less than half damage, pet gets nothing<P>OLD VERSION, GROUPED:<BR>-Pet does more than half damage in a group of N players, it takes <B>1/(N+1)</B> exp. Group splits the remaining <B>N/(N+1)</B> of exp.  <B> Depending on how many are in your group, 1/(N+1) ranges from 14% to 50%.</B><BR>- Pet does less than half damage, pet takes nothing.<P>NEW VERSION, SOLO:<BR>-Pet does ALL damage, takes 75% exp.<BR>-You do as little as one point of damage, pet takes <B>25% to 50%</B> exp.<BR>-You do more than half damage, you take 100% exp.<P>NEW VERSION, GROUPED:<BR>-Pet does ALL damage, takes 75% exp. Group splits remaining 25%.<BR>-Your group does as little as one point of damage, pet takes <B>25% to 50%</B> of group exp. Group splits remaining <B>50% to 75%</B>.<BR>-Your group does more than half damage, group splits 100% exp.<P><BR>Now when we compare, there are four results that nobody can argue with:<P>1. In the case of memblured or outdamaged pets, nothing has changed.  Exp of 100% now is the same as 100% before.<P>Ain't it great?  People who were playing well before are still rewarded for doing so. I like rewards for good play.<P>2. In the case of pet solo kills, there has been a reduction by HALF (you get 25% now, you got 50% before) in experience gained.  <P>This is no big deal. If you were letting your pet KS you without doing ANYTHING before, you probably don't care about the difference between 50% and 25% now.<P><BR>3. There are two small nerfs to DC in large groups.<P>A. DC pets used to be capped at 14% exp suck in a 6 man group in normal combat.  Now they can take 25% to 50% of group experience.  Obviously a nerf, but not a big one in a good group.<P>Still, I think this change was poorly thought out. Pets are used to tank adds in mez proof places, where they often do 50% damage to the add before the party engages.  In this situation, the DC pet becomes a liability.  There are enough bigots in Norrath to blow this up into a good reason for us to get rid of our pets.<P>B. DC pets can suck up to 75% of group experience from an 'untouched' mob in a 6 man group, where previously they could get only 14%.  This is the largest magnitude nerf.<P>This is unimportance, because it is SUCH an unusual scenario.  Swing that shissar, mates, and get yer 50%!<P>4. Small, low damage groups can lose a lot of exp to DC.  Previously, a group of enchanter and healer could count on pet taking 33% flat with no memory blur.  Now they can virtually count on the pet taking 50%. That's a 24% reduction in experience.<P>This is a significant nerf.  The fast-pull, fast-kill, power duo style is becoming more and more common.  The big difference between DC soloing and DC duoing for enchanters is that there typically isn't time to mem blur in a duo.  Stuff dies in seconds, and you are off to get another thing to kill. I think Verant wanted to slow these folks down some, and these changes do that.  Is it fair?  I think it balances out for the skilled player, who can do pull fast enough that this is still efficient.
</FONT>
